    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Policy Cost\"\nformat:\n  html:\n    fig-width: 8\n    fig-height: 6\n---\n\n\n::: {.callout-important collapse=\"true\"}\n## Additional Analysis: Correlation to Voluntary\n\nFormula for total cost To accurately budget for the increase, calculate the following for the entire company or for the employees receiving the raise:\\((\\text{Total\\ Current\\ Base\\ Salary}\\times 1.06)\\times (1+\\text{Burden\\ Rate})-(\\text{Total\\ Current\\ Base\\ Salary}\\times (1+\\text{Burden\\ Rate}))\\)The \"Burden Rate\" represents the cost of employer-paid benefits and taxes, usually estimated between 25% and 40% of an employee's base salary. \n\n:::\n\n# Analysis Overview\n\nUtilizing the current active employee population, we need to calculate the following items:\n\n* The current base compensation (I have convert the hourly workers to year compensation)\n* New compensation with 6% raise\n* Burden rate (estimated between 25% and 40% of employee's base salary)\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n\n\n# Analysis Overview\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code  code-fold=\"true\"}\nemp_clean |> \n  summarise(TotalCompensation = sum(EffectiveSalary, na.rm=T)) |> \n  ungroup() |> \n  mutate(NewComp = TotalCompensation * 1.06) |> \n  mutate(IncreaseDuetoRaise = NewComp - TotalCompensation) |> \n  mutate(Burden_25 = IncreaseDuetoRaise * 0.25,\n          Burden_40 = IncreaseDuetoRaise * 0.4) |> \n  mutate(TotalCost_25 = Burden_25 + IncreaseDuetoRaise,\n          TotalCost_40 = Burden_40 + IncreaseDuetoRaise) |> \n  pivot_longer(cols = 1:7) |>   \n  flextable()\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"tabwid\"><style>.cl-294572de{}.cl-2935b43e{font-family:'Arial';font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 1.00);background-color:transparent;}.cl-2935b452{font-family:'Arial';font-size:10pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 1.00);background-color:transpare